<p><strong>Installation of Jekyll:</strong></p>

<p>There is a lot of great Documentation on how to install Jekyll on you device. Head on over to the <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/installation/">Jekyll Docs</a> and that should get you squared away. Since I am on Windows I followed the instructions <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/installation/windows/">here</a>.</p>

<p>Now that I have Jekyll and friends installed I am going to open my command prompted. First Iâ€™ve checked my ruby and gem versions. then I switched to my Documents directory where I will host my site, then I created a new folder for my site name <strong><em>testsite</em></strong> I then ran the cmd Jekyll new testblog.
<img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll1.png" /></p>

<p>now open testblog</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>cd testblog
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Next we are going to head over to GitHub Page for the <a href="https://github.com/jekyll/minima">Minima Theme</a>
Make sure you are logged in and click the Fork button on the top right of the page.
<img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll2.png" /></p>

<p>This will create this repo under your name. Go to you profile and click on this repo.
There are several ways to go about this but rename your repository to username.github.io in order for git to recognize this repository as you hosted website. for instance mine is <a href="https://aaayejaaaye.github.io/">aaayejaaaye.github.io</a> @https://aaayejaaaye.github.io/.
I recommend going to the documentation for <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub Pages</a> and checking that out to see more on how this works, including documentation on Jekyll implementation.
Now we are going to open this new repo folder in Atom.
Go to file&gt;open Folder and select the â€˜minimaâ€™ folder.
make note of the file structure:</p>

<p><img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll3.png" /></p>

<p>save the project and go to you cmd prompt and navigate to the minima folder. See how atom and cmd match</p>

<p><img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll4.png" /></p>

<p><strong>Design Stuff:</strong></p>

<p>On The <a href="https://github.com/jekyll/minima">Minima Theme Page</a> and the <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/step-by-step/01-setup/">Jekyll Site</a> they explain really well just what all you are looking at. There are also some great <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iWowJBRMtpc&amp;t=442s">YouTube Tutorials</a>. Iâ€™m going to focus more on the extras like MD formatting CSS, HTML and creating custom files.
First thing Edit your _config.yml file.
 You will se alot of presets go ahead and fill those in. Here are my relevant Presets:</p>

<p><img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll7.png" /></p>

<p>save the changes and go back to your cmd prompt:</p>
