<p><strong><em>Creating a Banner</em></strong></p>

<p>You also may have seen the _includes folder read up on it <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/includes/">here</a>. This was the second hardest for me to grasps initially but once I understood it wasnâ€™t so bad. still a beginner tho. I wanted to have my own logo up instead of just my default name. So I am going to head to our  header.html file and using simple link and image tag I included my banner which I saved to my _picture folder.</p>

<p><img src="\pictures\how I Created My Blog\installjekyll012.png" /></p>

<p>My custom code is the &lt;a&gt; tag to create the link and in between that I have the &lt;img&gt; that is the link to my LOGO. I also did I similar thing to footer.html to include and image in there.
BTW, I created all my Logos with <a href="https://www.canva.com/">Canva</a>, I love it!</p>

<p><strong><em>Preivew Blog on Main Page</em></strong></p>

<p>You may have noticed that I have a little exceprt on the main page for each blog post, this is by design. I use a excerpt_separator variable and the  &lt;!â€“moreâ€“&gt;
 lets it no where the excerpt ends, observe:
